202
00:13:49,481 --> 00:13:50,997
What do I have here?

203
00:13:51,693 --> 00:13:54,375
I have a diffusion equation.

204
00:13:55,896 --> 00:14:01,013
So we have confirmed that at least
in this simple case as an illustration,

205
00:14:01,013 --> 00:14:03,719
this coefficient D indeed

206
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,496
<i>is</i> a diffusion coefficient

207
00:14:06,496 --> 00:14:09,547
because it's the coefficient that appears
in a diffusion equation

208
00:14:10,064 --> 00:14:13,561
for the density of the plasma species j.

209
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,436
Now a further consideration is that,

210
00:14:16,436 --> 00:14:19,936
plasmas tend to be quasi-neutral.

211
00:14:19,991 --> 00:14:22,773
In other words, the density 
of electrons and ions

212
00:14:22,773 --> 00:14:25,726
- presumed singularly 
charged -

213
00:14:26,439 --> 00:14:29,410
for simplicity, have to be equal.

214
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:35,478
So that means that the fluxes
need to be equal for electrons and ions,

215
00:14:35,740 --> 00:14:38,681
or quasi-neutrality
will not be maintained.

216
00:14:38,725 --> 00:14:43,574
And in general, diffusion coefficients
-as the mobilities- are different

217
00:14:43,574 --> 00:14:45,484
for ions and electrons,
so what happens?

218
00:14:45,484 --> 00:14:46,893
What can the plasma do?

219
00:14:46,893 --> 00:14:49,821
The plasma in fact, 
will set up an electric field

220
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:55,243
that will tend to slow down 
the faster of the two species

221
00:14:55,503 --> 00:14:58,856
and accelerate the slower
of the two species

222
00:14:58,868 --> 00:15:02,461
so that actually, the two fluxes
will be balanced.

223
00:15:04,197 --> 00:15:08,123
This is a general property in the plasma,
we'll derive it here,

224
00:15:08,123 --> 00:15:13,031
specifically for the case 
of unmagnetized plasmas or B₀ = 0

225
00:15:13,031 --> 00:15:15,020
because it is simpler.

226
00:15:15,273 --> 00:15:20,002
So we assume equal densities again
for ions and electrons,

227
00:15:20,062 --> 00:15:21,469
we call it n.

228
00:15:22,628 --> 00:15:24,229
Let's write the fluxes.

